title.narrative: 5.2 VULNERABLE GIRLS AND BOYS HAVE ACCESS TO AND USE WATER & SANITATION SERVICES

description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, including those with disabilities, have access to, and use, adequate, safe, affordable and sustainable water and sanitation services, which contributes to Environmental Sustainability, Sanitation, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Vulnerable people have access to safe drinking water, clean environment, and key hygiene/water conservation practices.

title.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, including those with disabilities, have access to, and use, adequate, safe, affordable and sustainable water and sanitation services

description.narrative: More than 112,000 people residing in Syrian Refugee Camps accessed sustained WASH services and over 32,000 people in vulnerable communities across the country were reached with improved water and sanitation systems with UNICEF Jordan support. Throughout 2020, UNICEF continued to support the MWI in reducing the strain on the overstretched water and sanitation infrastructure and services, progressing towards universal access to sustainable services in line with the Sustainable Development Goals, and strengthening the humanitarian-development nexus through advocating and implementing climate-resilient water and sanitation projects. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:26/08/2020
